Armis: Results
MITRE Engenuity does not assign scores, rankings, or ratings. The evaluation results are available to the public, so other organizations may provide their own analysis and interpretation - these are not endorsed or validated by MITRE.
 

Previous Next

Alerting Strategy

Armis collects data via deep packet inspections and by ingesting data from external sources, and then creates insights which translate into alerts that are categorized into threats, abnormal behaviour, suspicious connections, where each is tagged with the relevant Tactics and Techniques.

Correlation Strategy

Armis collects data from both network and integration sources and correlates them to relevant devices, consequently laying them on a timeline outlining a sequence of events. The Armis policy engine allows correlating events (activities, connections, device properties, time factors) which empowers users to receive alerts with rich contextual information.
